# Weather Explorer — environment variables
#
# This product is KEYLESS and privacy-first by design (NFR-COST-01, BC-PRIVACY-*).
# All third-party data comes from free, keyless services:
#   - Open-Meteo forecast + geocoding API (no key)   — TC-STACK-03
#   - OpenStreetMap raster tiles (no key, attribution required) — TC-STACK-04, TC-MAP-01
#
# There are therefore NO required secrets to run, build, or deploy this app.
# No analytics, no trackers, no application-set cookies (BC-PRIVACY-01/03).

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional configuration (safe to leave unset)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Absolute base URL of the deployed site, used to build absolute share links
# (?lat=&lon=&name=). Falls back to the request origin when unset.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://weather-explorer.example.com

# Override the Open-Meteo API origins only if self-hosting a mirror. Defaults to
# the public keyless endpoints when unset. Never put a secret here — there is none.
# OPEN_METEO_FORECAST_BASE=https://api.open-meteo.com
# OPEN_METEO_GEOCODING_BASE=https://geocoding-api.open-meteo.com

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Verification tooling (Phase 6) — not required at runtime
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BASE_URL: where check-a11y.mjs / chrome-devtools MCP point during E2E/a11y runs.
# BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
